        public GroupNodeElement(String name,
                        PlainEventListProxy propositions,
                        Map<String,String> attributes,
                        Collection<? extends NodeProxy> immediateChildNodes,
                        BoxGeometryProxy geometry)
        Creates a new group node.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the new group node.
        propositions - The list of propositions of the new group node, or null if empty.
        attributes - The attribute map of the new group node, or null if empty.
        immediateChildNodes - The set of immediate child nodes of the new group node, or null if empty.
        geometry - The geometric information of the new group node, or null.

      • GroupNodeElement

        public GroupNodeElement(String name)
        Creates a new group node using default values. This constructor creates a group node with an empty list of propositions, an empty attribute map, an empty set of immediate child nodes, and the geometric information set to null.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the new group node.

This method must return one of the leaf interfaces of the proxy hierarchy, e.g. EventProxy, not any specific implementation class.
